To switch from using **Prism.js** for syntax highlighting to leveraging **Markdown's** built-in capabilities, you'll need to make several adjustments to your `src/panelview.ts` file. This involves removing Prism.js dependencies, updating the HTML and CSS to support Markdown-based highlighting, and modifying the JavaScript to handle code block rendering appropriately.

Below are the detailed steps and corresponding code modifications:

---

## 1. Remove Prism.js Dependencies

### **File:** `src/panelview.ts`

### **Location:** `getHtmlForWebview` Method

#### **Before:**

```typescript:path/to/src/panelview.ts
private getHtmlForWebview(webview: vscode.Webview): string {
    const nonce = getNonce();
    const prismCssPath = vscode.Uri.joinPath(this._context.extensionUri, 'media', 'prism.css');
    const prismJsPath = vscode.Uri.joinPath(this._context.extensionUri, 'media', 'prism.js');
    const markedJsPath = vscode.Uri.joinPath(this._context.extensionUri, 'media', 'marked.js'); // Path to Marked.js
    const prismCssUri = webview.asWebviewUri(prismCssPath);
    const prismJsUri = webview.asWebviewUri(prismJsPath);
    const markedJsUri = webview.asWebviewUri(markedJsPath); // URI for Marked.js
    const workspaceFolderPath = vscode.workspace.workspaceFolders?.[0]?.uri.fsPath;

    return `
    <!DOCTYPE html>
    <html lang="en">
    <!-- ... other HTML content ... -->

    <!-- Prism.js CSS -->
    <link href="${prismCssUri}" rel="stylesheet" />
    <!-- Marked.js -->
    <script src="${markedJsUri}" nonce="${nonce}"></script>

    <!-- ... other HTML content ... -->

    <!-- Prism.js JS -->
    <script src="${prismJsUri}" nonce="${nonce}"> </script>

    <script nonce="${nonce}">
        // ... existing JavaScript code ...

        function attachCommitToggleListeners() {
            const commitHeaders = document.querySelectorAll('.commit-header');
            commitHeaders.forEach(header => {
                header.addEventListener('click', () => {
                    const details = header.nextElementSibling;
                    if (details) {
                        if (details.style.display === 'block') {
                            details.style.display = 'none';
                        } else {
                            details.style.display = 'block';
                            const codeBlocks = details.querySelectorAll('pre code');
                            Prism.highlightElement(block);
                        }
                    }
                });
            });
        }

        // ... other JavaScript code ...
    </script>
    </html>
    `;
}
```

#### **After:**

```typescript:path/to/src/panelview.ts
private getHtmlForWebview(webview: vscode.Webview): string {
    const nonce = getNonce();
    const markedJsPath = vscode.Uri.joinPath(this._context.extensionUri, 'media', 'marked.js'); // Path to Marked.js
    const markedJsUri = webview.asWebviewUri(markedJsPath); // URI for Marked.js
    const workspaceFolderPath = vscode.workspace.workspaceFolders?.[0]?.uri.fsPath;

    return `
    <!DOCTYPE html>
    <html lang="en">
    <!-- ... other HTML content ... -->

    <!-- Remove Prism.js CSS and JS -->
    <!-- <link href="${prismCssUri}" rel="stylesheet" /> -->
    <!-- <script src="${prismJsUri}" nonce="${nonce}"> </script> -->

    <!-- Marked.js -->
    <script src="${markedJsUri}" nonce="${nonce}"></script>

    <style nonce="${nonce}">
        /* ... existing CSS styles ... */

        /* Add styles for Markdown-based syntax highlighting */
        pre {
            background-color: var(--vscode-textCodeBlock-background);
            padding: 8px;
            border-radius: 3px;
            font-family: var(--vscode-editor-font-family);
            overflow-x: auto;
        }
        code {
            font-family: var(--vscode-editor-font-family);
            font-size: 0.9em;
            background-color: var(--vscode-textCodeBlock-background);
            padding: 2px 4px;
            border-radius: 3px;
        }

        /* Optional: Add basic syntax highlighting using CSS */
        /* Example for JavaScript */
        code.language-javascript {
            color: #dcdcdc;
        }
        /* Add more language-specific styles as needed */
    </style>

    <script nonce="${nonce}">
        // ... existing JavaScript code ...

        function attachCommitToggleListeners() {
            const commitHeaders = document.querySelectorAll('.commit-header');
            commitHeaders.forEach(header => {
                header.addEventListener('click', () => {
                    const details = header.nextElementSibling;
                    if (details) {
                        if (details.style.display === 'block') {
                            details.style.display = 'none';
                        } else {
                            details.style.display = 'block';
                            // Remove Prism.highlightElement as it's no longer needed
                            // Prism.highlightElement(block);
                        }
                    }
                });
            });
        }

        function formatResponse(responseText) {
            if (typeof responseText !== 'string') {
                console.warn('formatResponse received non-string responseText:', responseText);
                return '<em>Invalid response text.</em>';
            }

            // Use marked.js to parse and render Markdown content with syntax highlighting
            const markdownContent = marked.parse(responseText, {
                gfm: true,
                breaks: true,
                highlight: function(code, lang) {
                    // Optional: Implement basic syntax highlighting or integrate another library
                    return \`<pre><code class="language-\${lang}">\${escapeHtml(code)}</code></pre>\`;
                }
            });

            return markdownContent;
        }

        // ... other JavaScript code ...
    </script>
    </html>
    `;
}
```

### **Explanation:**

1. **Remove Prism.js Imports:**
   - **CSS Removal:** Delete the `<link>` tag that imports `prism.css`.
   - **JS Removal:** Delete the `<script>` tag that imports `prism.js`.

2. **Update JavaScript:**
   - **Remove Prism Highlighting:** Comment out or remove the `Prism.highlightElement(block);` line, as Prism is no longer used.
   - **Use `marked.js` for Rendering:** Utilize `marked.js` to parse Markdown content, which can handle code block rendering.

3. **Update CSS:**
   - **Define Code Block Styles:** Add CSS styles for `<pre>` and `<code>` elements to ensure that code blocks are displayed correctly.
   - **Optional Syntax Highlighting:** Implement basic syntax highlighting using CSS classes like `.language-javascript`. For more advanced highlighting, consider integrating another library or using a CSS framework that supports syntax highlighting.

---

## 2. Update JavaScript to Remove Prism Highlighting

### **File:** `src/panelview.ts`

### **Location:** `<script>` Section within `getHtmlForWebview` Method

#### **Before:**

```javascript:src/panelview.ts
